U.S. officials suspected that there would be another confrontation between Trump and Zelensky, due to the management of negotiations on the mineral agreement. "For several days, the Ukrainians teased us with this mineral affair, and today was the turning point," said a senior U.S. official. "The white check era for Zelensky in Washington is over and he didn't realize it." For their part, the Ukrainians were furious because Trump tried to impose an agreement initially unbalanced, at a time when the United States was already excluding them from talks with Russia about the future of Ukraine. And while the Friday meeting was in progress, Zelensky showed clearly frustrated for being warned about the situation that is experiencing his own country.&nbsp;
<h2><br> Germany, lite Trump-Zelensky "new era of infamy" ></h2>
The Trump-Zelensky dispute shows that "a new era of infamy began". German Foreign Minister Annalena Baerbock said this last night during a television broadcast. Today Baerbock added that the "unspeakable" quarrel to the White House between Trump and Zelensky to the White House resembles a "bad dream". &nbsp;
<h2> <br> Steinmeier, "Trump has humiliated a partner"> </h2>
German President Frank-Walter Steinmeier criticized Trump in unusually harsh terms for his behavior during the meeting last night with Kiev's leader. "The diplomacy fails when negotiating partners are humiliated in front of the whole world," said Steinmeier at the German press agency Dpa, during a flight to Uruguay. "The scene at the White House yesterday took my breath away. I would never have believed that one day we should protect Ukraine&nbsp; from the United States," said the German president.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>Finland, "Kiev is fighting for European security"></h2>
Finnish President Alexander Stubb reiterated today, following the White House's confrontation between Trump and Zelenski, his support for Ukraine, a country that, in his opinion, is also fighting for European security. "Ukraine &nbsp; is fighting not only for its independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity, but also for European security, freedom and an international order based on rules," said Stubb in a message published on his social X account, in which he mentioned the defense of Kiev by Russian aggression.
"Ukraine &nbsp; and its elected leaders democratically deserve our respect and support," said Stubb. "The fight against the Russian aggression war is about the defense of the existence of Ukraine &nbsp; as a nation. In Finland, we understand what is going through Ukraine," added the Finnish head of state, referring to the history of its country, which was also marked by conflicts with the Soviet Union in the last century. Stubb joins a group of European political leaders and personalities who supported Zelensky after his visit to the Oval Studio.&nbsp;
