AGI - Egyptian Prime Minister Mustafa Madbuli met in Cairo his Palestinian counterpart, Mohamed Mustafa, to discuss details of the plan of resumption and reconstruction of the Gaza Strip. The plan will be presented at the emergency summit of the Arab League scheduled for March 4 in Egypt.
During the meeting, Madbuli noted that, in accordance with the guidelines of Egyptian President Abdel Fattah al-Sisi, "the Egyptian government prepared an integrated plan for the prompt resumption and reconstruction of the Gaza Strip, maintaining Palestinian citizens within it even during the reconstruction process."
The statement does not provide further details on the plan that Egypt will present to the leaders of the 22 countries of the Arab League. The Egyptian Prime Minister reiterated Egypt's firm support for Palestine and its legitimate rights, in particular the right to self-determination and independence of the Palestinian State under the conditions of 4 June 1967, with East Jerusalem as capital. &nbsp;

